The suspect was arrested following a tip-off from members of the public. [File, Standard]  Detectives at the Directorate of Criminal Investigations have arrested a 27-year-old Ugandan woman suspected of trafficking hard drugs.  The detectives say Bizu Rubi was arrested at a hotel on Jogoo road following a tip-off from a member of the Public.  “She is believed to have been waiting for her Kenyan contact to deliver the drugs (heroin) to him,” DCI tweeted.  According to a Tweet by the DCI, the pellets were carefully concealed as potato crisps.  Ruiru police gun down robbery with violence suspect  Haji alleges plot to kick him out of office as row with Kinoti escalates  Two suspects burnt to death for snatching man’s phone on Jogoo Road  MCAs indict Elachi over irregular staff promotions, demand probe by EACC The suspect was arrested and 30 pellets of the highly addictive drug recovered from her, police say.  She is in police custody awaiting arraignment.   Bogus Degrees: DCI, EACC and IEBC to track culprits, team to hunt people with fake certificates  Former Governor Mike Sonko detained at DCI headquarters; he is to face robbery and assault charges  Sonko Summoned: Sonko expected to present himself at DCI to record a statement on his sentiments By Kamore Maina | 3 hours ago By James Omoro | 4 hours ago By Benard Sanga | 4 hours ago By James Omoro | 4 hours ago